reviewText:
There's not much to be said about the game. There's a story here, but you won't be paying much attention to it because your eyes will be jumping around in a constant frenzy between screen and keyboard. The graphics are okay-ish, there's a lot of swearing (thank God, because I do hate narrow-minded political correctness), and the script comes straight out one of those Grind movies from the eighties (or seventies, not sure).

Gameplay feels great - provided you like typing, that is. If you don't, there's no point in getting this title, is there? The words are thrown at you in a way designed to keep you on your toes, and most of them are quite funny and there are keywords/catch phrases from other games, movies and TV shows. These will bring a smile to your lips when you spot them for what they are. And there are times when it really feels like you are shooting a gun instead of typing on your keyboard.

Each level (story chapter) ends with a boss fight. Bosses are creative, but you defeat them always in the same manner (you've guessed it, more typing).

You can fiddle with the options to adjust your typing response time, but I think that even the lowest setting won't help you much if you only type with two fingers. Finger dexterity is a requirement here. Or not, since story mode gives you unlimited lives.

There are some other game types besides story mode, but I haven't explored those and can't really comment on them.

To sum it all up, get this game if:
>you really like typing;
>you like zombies;
>you are not easily offended by violence and/or swear words;
>it's on sale.
